{
  "texts": [
    "Formally, let B(I) denote all possible bounding boxes in I:b pred = arg max b∈B(I) ϕ(I, Q, b),where ϕ(I, Q, b) measures the alignment between the visual content in b and the semantic information in Q.",
    "Unlike conventional object detection, where the model simply recognizes and localizes pre-defined object categories, visual grounding requires a joint understanding of both visual cues and the linguistic nuances embedded in Q.",
    "Here, f vis (I, b) and f lang (Q) denote visual and linguistic representations, respectively, and we defineϕ(I, Q, b) = sim f vis (I, b), f lang (Q),with sim(•, •) as a similarity metric (e.g., cosine).",
    "The challenge is to optimize this objective in a zero-shot setting without task-specific fine-tuning.GroundingAgent We proposed, GroundingAgent, a training-free framework for zero-shot visual grounding.",
    "As shown in Figure 2, a pretrained open-vocabulary detector first suggests candidate bounding boxes."
  ]
}